  "question_html": "<p>A temperature difference can generate e.m.f. in some materials. Let <b>S</b> be the e.m.f. produced per unit temperature difference between the ends of a wire, <b>σ</b> the electrical conductivity and <b>κ</b> the thermal conductivity of the material of the wire. Taking <i>M, L, T, I</i> and <i>K</i> as dimensions of mass, length, time, current and temperature, respectively, the dimensional formula of the quantity <b>$Z = \\frac{S^2 \\sigma}{\\kappa}$</b> is :</p>",
  "options": [
    {
      "label": "a",
      "html": "<div class=\"shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-white text-sm rounded-[50%] w-[25px] h-[25px] bg-blue-600  \">A</div>  <div class=\"grow question xl:text-lg\"><p>[M<sup>0</sup>L<sup>0</sup>T<sup>0</sup>I<sup>0</sup>K<sup>0</sup>]</p></div> "
    },
    {
      "label": "b",
      "html": "<div class=\"shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-white text-sm rounded-[50%] w-[25px] h-[25px] bg-blue-600  \">B</div>  <div class=\"grow question xl:text-lg\"><p>[M<sup>0</sup>L<sup>0</sup>T<sup>0</sup>I<sup>0</sup>K<sup>−1</sup>]</p></div> "
    },
    {
      "label": "c",
      "html": "<div class=\"shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-white text-sm rounded-[50%] w-[25px] h-[25px] bg-blue-600  \">C</div>  <div class=\"grow question xl:text-lg\"><p>[M<sup>1</sup>L<sup>2</sup>T<sup>−2</sup>I<sup>−1</sup>K<sup>−1</sup>]</p></div> "
    },
    {
      "label": "d",
      "html": "<div class=\"shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-white text-sm rounded-[50%] w-[25px] h-[25px] bg-blue-600  \">D</div>  <div class=\"grow question xl:text-lg\"><p>[M<sup>1</sup>L<sup>2</sup>T<sup>−4</sup>I<sup>−1</sup>K<sup>−1</sup>]</p></div> "
    }
  ],
  "answer": {
    "type": "mcq_single",
    "value": "b"
  },
  "explanation_html": "<p>S is emf per unit temperature ⇒  </p>\n<p>$$[S]=\\frac{[V]}{[K]}=\\frac{M\\,L^2\\,T^{-3}\\,I^{-1}}{K}              =M\\,L^2\\,T^{-3}\\,I^{-1}\\,K^{-1}.$$</p><p></p>\n<p></p><p>σ is electrical conductivity ⇒  </p>\n<p>$$[σ]=\\frac{[J]}{[E]}          =\\frac{I\\,L^{-2}}{M\\,L\\,T^{-3}\\,I^{-1}}          =M^{-1}\\,L^{-3}\\,T^3\\,I^2.$$</p><p></p>\n<p></p><p>κ is thermal conductivity ⇒  </p>\n<p>$$[κ]=\\frac{\\dot Q/(A)}{∇T}          =\\frac{M\\,L^2\\,T^{-3}/L^2}{K\\,L^{-1}}          =M\\,L\\,T^{-3}\\,K^{-1}.$$</p><p></p>\n<p></p><p>Now  </p>\n<p>$$[Z]      =[S]^2\\,[σ]\\,[κ]^{-1}      =(M\\,L^2\\,T^{-3}\\,I^{-1}\\,K^{-1})^2       \\times M^{-1}\\,L^{-3}\\,T^3\\,I^2       \\times (M\\,L\\,T^{-3}\\,K^{-1})^{-1}$$</p>\n<p>Simplifying exponents gives  </p>\n<p>$$[Z]=M^0\\,L^0\\,T^0\\,I^0\\,K^{-1}.$$</p><p></p>\n\n<p>Answer: Option B.</p>"
}